 {"id":"bd-9i2v","title":"Audit and fix silent Result discards in btrfs write/unlink/truncate paths","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-02-20T02:08:00.606377012Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-20T02:23:43.043605909Z","closed_at":"2026-02-20T02:23:43.043583487Z","close_reason":"Propagated errors in btrfs write path (inline-to-regular conversion, device write, tree insert). Added warn! logging to 8 cleanup paths (truncate, unlink dir_item/dir_index/inode_ref, rename dotdot). All gates pass.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"bd-9vft","title":"Fix dirty tracking bugs in ARC cache flush paths","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-03-21T08:12:24.234830612Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-21T08:12:35.468375244Z","closed_at":"2026-03-21T08:12:35.467685107Z","close_reason":"Fixed 2 bug classes in ARC cache flush:\n(1) CRITICAL: flush_pending_evictions never called clear_dirty after writing blocks to device — dirty counts stayed inflated forever, causing false backpressure and potential infinite loop. Added clear_dirty loop after successful flush.\n(2) HIGH: All 3 flush paths (flush_pending_evictions, flush_dirty_batch, flush_dirty) incorrectly restored already-persisted blocks as dirty when repair notification failed. Blocks were already on disk; re-marking them dirty caused unnecessary re-writes and count inflation. Changed to log-and-continue since repair notification is non-critical. 232 ffs-block tests pass.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["block","cache","correctness"]}
